1�In other words, the crystal was losing the power it needed to sustain Al'Taieu in the other dimension.
1�Yep.The weakened state of this overgrown quartz is the reason that the Keeper of the Apocalypse is threatening to descend upon Vana'diel.
1�I'm sure you've noticed it by now,  .Your ability to hear the whisper of the soul...
1�Passed through the medium of the amulet, the light gathered from the four crystals has changed you.
1�Selh'teus!If you mean to save both the world and everyone in it, then someone inhuman like you or me should be sacrificed!
1�And you, Tenzen!Phoenix, the avatar of rebirth, can't have led you this far just to snuff out  's life!
1�Surely she meant to resurrect the shattered pieces of  's spirit using her own lifeforce!
1�I was the Keeper of the Apocalypse once.I know only too well the fear and horror that await us.
1�But you gotta listen to me, Selh'teus!Pour the energy of the fifth mothercrystal into  !
1�?[His/Her] victories against the Emptiness and everything else we've faced have not been won through the power of the four crystals alone.
1�  has an inner strength.A spirit that loves this world and those who dwell upon it.
1�That's why I believe ?[he/she] will prevail against the keeper!
1�Selh'teus!Open the way to Al'Taieu!
e!�Dammit...This is because of Nag'molada.
1�When Naggy was absorbed, all of his knowledge poured straight into the mind of the Twilight God!
1� , I'm gonna need the amulet back.
1�We gotta go!He's in the lowest level of the palace!
.)�(But it was not a complete separation.)
1�(After the Crystal Line was reactivated, energy was siphoned from the fifth mothercrystal...)
1�(Drawing it and the city of Al'Taieu back to Vana'diel.)
1�(However, I am a child of darkness. I could never be the bearer of light.)
1�(I needed a worthy receptacle for that power. I needed you.)
1�(Your journey has been for the sake of the crystal.)
1�(Your adventure is now at an end.)
1�(Return,  . Return to the light of the crystal.)
1�But why does only this crystal glow with such a strange incandescence...?
1�The air here is so chilly.The other crystals exuded such a sense of warmth and peace...
1�The return of Al'Taieu and the arrival of the keeper will be prevented.
1�This solution was discovered by the boy Selh'teus--and by Phoenix, the fiery bird of rebirth.
1�That is why he has visited each of the remaining crystals in turn:To relieve them of their light and power...
1�And to pour that energy into the crystal that lies before us.
1�Phoenix referred to you as the ??Vessel of Light.??
1�Fated to be smashed open before the fifth mothercrystal...
1�Nag'molada!?
1�This is...the...fifth...?
1�So if...the power...of the crystal...is restored...!
1�This place...!
1�This is the crystal that the Wyrmking spoke of?
1�What happened...?
1�Sustain Al'Taieu?
1�I, too, wish for the way to be opened.
s?�??I will prevail against the deity that dwells beyond the Gate of the Gods. Open the way to Al'Taieu.??Weren't those the words you used?
1�Do you not find it unfair that only  �[she/he] should bear the sins of people?
1�We ancients are all responsible for these events.I shall shoulder my part of the burden.
1�Incredible...
1�Al'Taieu...You were meant to be impossible to find...
1�Ahahaha!Who would have thought the plan to open the Gate of the Gods would succeed?
1�Al'Taieu!Long have I yearned to behold your magnificent spires!
1�Why...?Why can't I hear the voices?
1�Why do I not hear the whispers of the Zilartian people or the Dawn Maiden?
1�Silence!
1�Your unruly thoughts are clouding my mind!
1�So, the rest of you were drawn into this world as well.How inconvenient...
1�A visit to the Grand Palace of Hu'Xzoi should bring some interesting encounters.Perhaps the Dawn Maiden is there...
1�There!I can see him!
1�There!I can see him!
1�There!I can see him!
1�He's gonna break the fifth mothercrystal and bring this entire city crashing down on the world!
d!�Wait!Take us with you!
1�The great Promathia realized why his children have not come to greet him!
1�Take us with you to Vana'diel!
1�That's right!
1�(Your death is the only way to save both Vana'diel and her people...)
1�Canst thou hear me, Goddess?Thou who hast sheltered my very existence.
1�I will be reborn.It is time to surrender to thine abhorred ??death,?? to the embrace of perpetual darkness.
1�An eternity of silence awaits.
1�Our farewell this time shall be forever.
1�Hey, did you guys see where Promathia went!?
1�Hey, did you guys see where Promathia went!?
1�Hey, did you guys see where Promathia went!?
1�The Goddess...is crying?
1�What was that!?The dusty old divinity is headed for Vana'diel!?
1�All have become one...
1�All have become one...
1�All have become one...
1�My master, his lady, their friends, everyone...

1�However, I cannot believe this is the Paradise of peace and love spoken of in legend.We have already been set upon by vicious beasts.
1�If Prishe was so intent on gaining entry to the palace, then the keeper will most likely be found inside...
1�Are you certain?I feel that the light has not abandoned us.
1�If we all stand together in body and spirit, there may still be a chance...
1�You mean to say that the light has not left us completely?
1�Then if we all stand together in body and spirit, perhaps there is a way...
1�You!Have you come to punish us!?
1�H-h-hold on a second!Time out! Time out!
1�It's not our fault!Lord Tenzen lied to us!
1�And if you don't follow your samurai master's orders, you have to commit ritual suicide.It's true! I read it in a book somewhere!
1�I suppose you want to get into the palace, huh?
1�Well, we want to get in there, too.This voice in my head is driving me crazy!
1�Let's let bygones be bygones and work together, okay?We've ditched the samurai life, anyway.
1�Getting past that gate is more complicated than just releasing the lock on this  �[southern/eastern/western] tower.
1�If you really want to know how to open the gate, you better take a look at the other towers as well.
1�Did we do it!?
1�Makki told me all about our deal!You wanna get in to see the king, right?
1�Just so's you know, the positions of princes and princess have already been filled!
1�They've been out of the picture for ten thousand years now, so he must be feeling pretty lonely.
1�After all that time, he's probably a few jewels short of a crown, too, if you know what I mean.I doubt the king'll notice if we're a little shorter than he remembers.
1�We might even take you on as a servant if you're lucky!C'mon, time's a wastin'! Off to the  �[southern/eastern/western] tower!

1�Is it open!?

1�You have our royal gratitude.
1�Prince Kukki has informed me of the situation, and I commend you on your wise decision.
1�We shall be sure to put in a good word for you with His Majesty.

1�I think it opened!
1�It seems...to be coming...from beyond...the gate...
1�What...do you mean...?
1�I have...no intention...of joining forces...with Nag'molada...
1�And if what Bahamut says is true, the Keeper of the Apocalypse lurks somewhere in this rrrealm.
1�First we have to find a way to open this gate.Let's get moving.
1�I hear a voice calling to me...
1�The portal appears to be locked.If we are to believe the talk of those beings, this path leads to the palace of the Zilartian king.
1�One of the inhabitants here spoke of a girl matching Prishe's description heading this way.If we can gain an audience with the king, we should learn exactly what's going on here.
1�!?This place lies beyond the Gate of the Gods?Did the ancients truly cross that legendary border!?
1�I worry that the Keeper of the Apocalypse will be beyond our ability.
1� .The four sources of light you acquired...
1�Were they not all taken from you by that blackheart, Nag'molada?
1�The people of this world have evolved into five unique species, each harboring a distinctive darkness.
1�Crystal warriors.Thou wert created to destroy those evils.
1�Yet even thy strength canst not prevail against this darkness.
1�Emptiness.'Tis the ever-present shadow of blessed light.
1�If this phenomenon represents complete death, then one could argue its presence was inevitable in a complete world.
1�Thus thou split the crystal for thy children's sake...
1�Is this not so, Great Goddess Altana...?
..�But this paradise did not last forever.
1�The enormous jewel was split into five parts, and this perfect realm degraded into an incomplete world...
1�We were reduced from the superior life forms of a higher plane into these flawed and insignificant forms.
1�Thus, we must gather and focus the energy of the crystals into opening a gate to that lost dimension.
1�We are both well aware of this predicament.
1�And yet, there is one thing I simply cannot understand:
1�How did this tragedy occur in the first place?
1�Why was the original stone shattered into five parts?Who is responsible for this incomprehensible act?
1�It all began with a stone...
1�In ages past, the five crystals existed as one enormous jewel that bathed the world in holy light.
1�This mystical light banished the Emptiness and brought forth mighty gods...
1�These gods cultivated their power and concentrated their energies.
1�They created a balance between the eight elements of the world without, and a harmony for the myriad senses of the world within.
1�And so, an eternal paradise blessed in all ways was born.
